  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Initiatives to safeguard intangible cultural heritage through formal and non-formal education for education quality improvement in Central Asia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">One of the priorities in the field of ICH for 2018-2021 is safeguarding ICH in formal and NFE. The Almaty Office will engage 4 cluster countries in activities focusing on safeguarding ICH through formal and NFE. It will focus on developing guidance for integrating ICH safeguarding in existing school programmes and activities. The objective is to encourage teachers to sensitize children, young people about the importance of their ICH. The activity will start by a survey on experiences of integrating ICH in education mapping out experiences on learning about ICH. It will be presented during a sub-regional meeting in 2019 with participants from MoE, institutes, national ICH Committees, who will discuss the existing experiences, develop guidance on integrating ICH in education.</narrative>
  </description>
